    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka schedules three-hour power cuts for Aug 24",
      "author": "Chanka Jayasinghe",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka will impose power cuts of up to three hours on August 24, Public Utilities Commission (PUCSL) Chairman Janaka Ratnayake said.",
        "All areas (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, P, Q, R, S, T, U, V and W) will have power cuts of 1 hours and 40 minutes between 01.30 pm and 06.00 pm and 1 hour 20 minutes from 06.00pm to 10.00 pm.",
        "Group CC will experience a 2 hour and 30-minute power cut from 6.00 am to 8.30 am.",
        "Groups M, N, O, X and Y which come under industrial zones will have a three-hour cut from 5.30 am to 8.30am.",
        "The state-run Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) said supply interruption time and restoration time will vary within 30 minutes as indicated above. (Colombo/Aug23/2022)"
      ],
